values: Alright, so the night wasn't so crazy, we all just stayed at our ridiculasly nice hotel all night and played pool and watch a couple movies.  The next day everyone went scubba diving but i just wasn't feeling it, so i stayed at layed out at the hotel all day, its such a hard life ya know....that whole day was just laxed.  When everyone got back we were all beat from the sun and slept, we didn't really go out at all, the only thing we did wasin the lobby of out hotel we meet with our tour guides students, she is an english teacher, we talked to thme for a hour or so, and sang songs, they sang us some songs in english that we didn't even know, they were really cool to meet.  They were all 19-20 and they do a lot of the same stuff we do, execpt it isn't "acceptable" for girls to go to bars or clubs, it is looked down upon, the other interesting thing i learned is that they don't start at age 0, they start at 1, so if they say they are 20, they were born in 1985, i found that really interesting.  After that, we went back to the hotel and just kicked it there again, we played pool and watched movies on HBO, nothing to crazy, but it was nice to relax for a while b/c we have all been doing so much stuff for weeks in a row.  The next day we all got up early and left our amazing hotel to go back to Saigon.  When we got back we went to the boat to drop off out stuff, then out driver Dihn came and picked us up.  He took us the to tuna factory he works at, it was so crazy.  We saw the whole proccess from gutting and de-boning to steaming to chopping up to canning, it was so crazy, then we talked to the main guy who told us they do about insane amount of tons of tuna a month, soemthing like 400 tons a month.  It was just a really interesting experiense because we learned so much about bussiness in general and how it works.  After the factory we went and got the guys suits done for a second fitting and then we went and did a little shopping and thne back to the boat.  I bought like 12 - 15 DVD' for like $1.50 a piece, so cheap, and i brought my comp down to the guy that was selling them to try them out it was good. So now i'm back on the boat and had a test, it was AMAZING!!!! he dosen't believe in protering tests and then the test said list, and it really ment only list, no explination or anything, and the essay part is take in cabin and is due then 2nd class after Thailand, i love this school!!!!

So, my last night in Hong Kong was just, WOW.  To start off i saw a Yellow B E A Utiful Skyline parked right behind a beautiful 575 Maranello (Ferrari) at this club then from there the night got better.  So i have come to a revalation, i'm just not feeling drinking so much anymore, in the past week i've drank once and i only had 2 drinks the whole night.  So i had 2 drinks in Hong Kong, didn't feel a thing, but i DANCED the whole freaking night away.  This girl from the Ship was so freaking drunk and when i was tring to dance with her she kept just like being all over, and a really drunk girl isn't attractive when you are sober, so i pawned her off on her freineds and kept on dancing, at one club i was up on a table with a girl at another there was a live band and we were ging crazy it was so fun!  Then later that night a few of us didn't want the night to end, so we went to this club in another part of town called Joe Bannana.  It was awsome, my friend Danielle bought a bottle of Vodka, and i take back what i said, i drank WAY later that night, we got to this club around 3, so she had a bottle i they made me drink....so i had like 4 vodka cranberry's in 30 - 60 min.  But nothing crazy happened after that, just got back to the ship late and crashed out.  The next day was fun too, i was so tired and done when i got back Hunter tried to make me up at like 830 - 9 to go out but i just didn't hear the phone so i endded up getting up around 1130 or so, it was all good i ran into my friends Erin and Lacey in the shopping center that was our port in Hong Kong and we went out and shopped to the same bazzar area we did before, only difference this time was i decided i'm doing my room safari and spent some good money on 3 awsome paintings for my room, so i was stoked on that, then later that night i eat at CPK in Hong Kong, CLASSIC!!!  Our next 2 days on the ship were pretty boring.....classes were the same, i have a test when i get back, a paper to turn in, the normal, nothing crazy.  Only cool thing was on sunday there was a huge BBQ on the top deck of the boat and all of us were chilling out in out swim suits in the pool eating BBQ.  It was fun, also the captian tested the engines and took them full speed of 29 Knots which is EXTREMELY fast for a big boat i guess, it was cool, it made a huge wake.  Next its on to Vietnam

So Beijing was a blast.  We stayed at the Great Wall Sheraton.  The 1st day we got in we got in about mid afternoon and after we packed and showered we went down to eat, Beau, his new girl Cassie, Hunter and I.  So we eat at the buffet,all i have to say is O M F G, it was probably one of the best resturants i've ever eatten at, we loaded our plates like 5 times over again, it was so good!  So, after our amazing dinner we wanted to go out.  So we went out to bar row.  A bunch of the SAS'ers were out there so it was cool, we all partied and drank the night away. We went into this one club that had a green strobe light, it was so crazy, just trippy.  We were all dancing on the tables in there it was fun.  Ha, Beau went to go onto one of the tables and slipped and fell and totally scared up the side of his leg, kind of funny.  So the next day we had Mr. Li pick us up.  We all went to The Great Wall of China, and all i have to say is, WOW!  It huge, we only saw one small section, it streches some 3000 - 4000 km, and over 7,000,000 people died building the wall, its about 1 per meter.  As we were climbing the wall saw some random things, like a sheep up there with some guy, so random, but i have a pic of me and the ship, CLASSIC!  After we were done climbing the wall we don't just take some stairs back down, we take a Tobagen, aka a slide!!! OMG, that was so much fun, you can get going so fast, almost like my car, HA, closest thing i've had to driving.  Ha, so another Beau got fucked up story, him and Cassie took a 2 person slide down, haha, they got going to fast and took the corner to fast and flipped and they are all scraped up, it was so F***ing funny.  After that we went shopping at the wall, i'm an offical tourist, i bought a I climbed The Great Wall t-shirt! haha.  So after that we all went back to the hotel and eat another great buffet, expect it was a Seafood night, but they still had filet and chicked and pita bread made in front of you! It was ridiculasly good.  So after our amzing dinner we went out clubbing again, 1st we started at bar row again, then after that we moved on the Club Banna, haha, it was so awsome, we went in then went up stairs VIP and had a table and wow, it was amzing, this trip just keeps getting better and better.  The next day we had to leave to Hong Kong, but not till 5pm, so we went out shopping, i got a SICK watch and Hunter got some shoes and a couple watchs, China is ridiculasly cheap. But the big deal of the shopping trip was Beau spending $300 US dollars.  He got 2 boxes full of clothes, and 3 louie bags, the shoulder ones, that are INSANLY good looking.  He had it all in what was equivelent to a 40 gallon trash bag.  After that, we had to rush and get to the airport, when we got there they made Beau go get boxes for his crap.  So we took the plane to Hong Kong, and when we got here all i have to say is WOW!  Cassie hooked us up with a room at the Sheaton Towers in Hong Kong, omg, one of the nicest hotels i've been to, its nothing like the Sheartons at home.  So we got in and got some dinner at the Cafe which was also very good.  Then we went out to this street that i can't pronounce the name of, Lan Quia Fong or something like that, it was SO much fun.  1st we went to some Irish pub and watched a bunch of drunk Russians and Brits drink and sing songs, it was so funny, then when that closed we went across the street and danced to this live band.  They were all asian, which is funny, b/c they sang everything from 50 cent in da club to Blink 182, but they were REALLY good, so we rocked out till about 4am and then met some guys from New York who are in for some huge diamond show at our hotel.  When we got back to the hotel, we went up to thier room, and cassie tried on this 13 karrot diamond bracelt, it was beautiful, but none of us had 14k on us so....no real intention of buying it.  These guys were Isreali, they were way cool.  So this brings me to today.  We woke up and Hunter and I went and met up with this girl he knows who lives in Hong Kong.  Beau and Cassie stayed at the hotel and went to the spa and etc.  Hunter and i went and say a little of Hong Kong, it is unbeliveable, probably one of the nicest towns ive ever been in, its amazing!!!!i could live here no problem.  So we went to some Thai resturant and got some Pad Tai, it was so good, we then went and shopped around the little Bazzar there and then went back to the hotel.  Beau and Cassie booked a room for tonight at the Westin thats on some little island right off Hong Kong, but Hunter and i decided to just stay on the boat.  So we left the hotel and walked to the boat, our port isn't just some ugly port.  Its a 4 floor shopping wall, not to metion that every name band in the world has a store about less then 1mi away, its unbelivabl.  So right now i'm in Hong Kong and im going to get ready for another fun night and see where it takes me!

Ok, so before i get to China, Pub night....haha, ok so the theme was a White Trash Bash....it was Classic, i guess a bunch of people got but hurt by it thou, b/c they said that it was being prejeduce or some bull shit, anyways thou, it was awsome, i drank a few to many beers, and the night got crazy...woke up and found random pics on my camera and one sandle in the bathroom and one somewhere in my room, haha, was a good night thou...alright, so we are now in China, this is NOTHING like Japan, 1st off, the people here speak a lot more english, its kind of wierd....the driving is like nothing you have ever seen, its make up your own lanes, and crossing the streets is like playing frogger, you have to watch for cars, buses, bikes and motorcycles b/c none of them stop for you.  Anyways today we just shopped around Shanghi.  Shanghi is unbelivable, its a city that belongs on Mars,there sky is full of Skyscrapers and crazy looking buldings, there are things that look like London and other parts of Europe and then things straight from Mars, its crazy.  So we went out shopping, found a bunch of fake crap, omg, you've never seen so much fake Louie in your life, i didn't get anythign, i can't really see the point of spending money to get shit...but then again, coming from Japan its not really spending money, here, a dollar goes a LONG!!!!! way....we had lunch for 5, and beers all around and extra stuff for about $20, it is ridiuclas.  So Beau found this new girl named Cassie, and all of a sudden they are attached at the hip, its kind of wierd, like 7  of us went to the market today and like 10 min in to it him and Cassie just took off to shop by themselves.  Kind of sucked, just b/c stick with your buddies...she left all her friends too...so right now its about 5am and i've pulled an all nighter b/c these stupid girls Kathryn and Sara said the airport is like a hour away and its like 20 min away and its stupid,so we are leaving for the airport to go to Bejing to go see the great wall of china in about 30 min and our flight leaves at 9 or so...i cant wait to see the wall, i think we go to see it tom, and today we'll prob go to Teinamen square, but it'll be a blast anyway!!!

Ok, so i`m in freaking Toyko right now, doing this from the 4th floor of the apple store, hahaha, how cool is this, anyways, i have another update i have on my laptop but i left that on the ship so i`ll add that when i get back to the ship, but it has been a crazy few days here in Japan, we arrived yesterday morning into Kobe at about 8am, then we had to wait for customs to check all of our passports so we got off the ship about 12 or so.  Alright, so Beau, Hunter, Doug and I left with 3 girls from Kobe to get to the train station to get to Toyko.  So 1st off, the lanuage barrier SUCKS!!! its wierd being the tourist....but 1st off the taxi driver took us to the station, but everyone had a rail pass that you have to rediem at the station across town, and i didn`t even have a ticket, so i had to get one....  So we get on the subway and go to the other station, we then go and get tickets and finally figure it out after spending 20 min trying to figure out what the fuck they are saying, and vis versa.  So then we think we are all set, nope.....now we have to walk what was right down the street that turned into a 30 min walk.....BACK to the same station we left the 1st time, kinda frustrating, but we get thru it.  We then get on the train, all of us guys have 1st class tickets, but the girls didn:t and we met up with another guy named Bo who also didn:t have a 1st class ticket.  So we get on the train and then the attendet comes by, none of us know what the fuck we are saying, he wants me to go to another car, and i:m like i want to sit with my friends......finally he just gets so frustrated he leaves, and all of us, even the ones w/o 1st class tickets stayed in he 1st class car.....so it was cool.  When we get to the station, everyone can tell we are not from here, go figure huh.....so this guy comes up to us named Diego....turns out he lived in SD for a bit, he was Japanse but he was out ther for a year or so.  So he starts helping us, we are trying to get to our hotel, the Four Seasons!!!!! haha, anyways so turns out it was right next to the train station.....however not the one we were staying at, so we all go catch a taxi and get over the other four seasons, it is AMAZING, its so nice, i have pics for everyone.....So us guys all have a room, but the girls just kinda tagged along, so we spent like 45 min figuring out what they are going to do......finallly they just say fuck it and end up getting a room at the four season to....We are all now starving and ready to eat, so we ask the consere to hook us up at a good sushi place, so they make reservations for us....it turns into a $40 cab ride then we go inside and sit and start looking at the menu.....$80 A PERSON!!!!! so we just drink out drinks and leave, which was still $70.  We then go down into some other town, Ra Ponge.....i think, either way, THAT WAS A BLAST!!!!!! Its just like New York....well, i hear since i:ve never been to NY, yet....anyways, so we find some other sushi place, was awsome, their 2nd day after remodeling, so drinks were free.  Ok now, i tried some wierd shit, no idea what it was, but i know i had octupus....that was kinda....interesting, anyways, it wasn:t bad dinner was like $15 which is WAY cheap for Japan, b/c its outgregous here,

So, now starts the parting, we must have gone to about 6 different bars, it was GREAT!!!!! all the girls kept getting free drinks and then giving them to us and then going and getting more, haha, classic night, it was great, but we got back the room about 2 or so b/c we wanted to be up early to go to the fish market.....so we got up early, REALLY fucking early, our call at 6 wakes us up, we get ready take a taxi out to the market that we were told by four seanson was open, to find out it was closed after another $30 taxi ride!  So now, its about 6;45 or so and we are in the middle of Toyko....We then have been walking for 6 hours....we walked ALL over toyko, it was crazy....i:m actually at the 4 story apple store right now righting this, anyways....we all finally got hungry and try to find somewhere to eat, which is REALLY hard when there is 7 of you....we then spend about 1 - 2 of those hours going in and out of resturants trying to figure where to eat....man....so we eat and now went over to the big mall where all the nice shops are....the watch i bought my Ex was $400 US more then at home, no wonder all those Asians come to us to by their stuff...hah....so we looked around and came here to the apple store only to find a free internet cafe HA so great, anyways thou, that is where my story leaves off, its been a blast and i:m sure more good tiems to come, only complant right now, is everyting is what Beau and Hunter want to do....i mean its okay, but would whatever, i always have a good time.......One more thing..the cars!!!!!! omg the cars, this is heven for me, all i do when i:m walking is stare at the street with my camera, i:ve seen like so many skylines like they are nothing, its just crazy.....anys, i:ll keep everyone posted on the next of my adventures

Ok, so tonight was WAY better then last night.  I met a couple guys that go to USD, Hunter and Beau, they are way cool guys.  They have a bunch of stuff planed around the world to every palce that we are going more my style, a lil more up class ya know, so i am excited that there are some people that are more like me here...  I went to this place called Shananigins tonight, it was cool, bunch of people from Sem at Sea were there, i am already known as the dancing guy, go figure....but it was cool, and then after i went and got some frys from Cautus Cafe, honestly the best frys i've ever had.... So tom is my last day in canada before i get on the ship, i'm excited to get on there and get this party going, i'm probably goign to get some alch to take with me on the ship, esp b/c its a 2 week boat ride till we get there,so should make things better....all in all, finally got better, got to see what tom had in store, hope its fun....email me whenever you get a chance, keep me intertaned and up to date on whats going, bigdog0@sbcglobal.net

Alright, so i arived here in Vancouver.....everything is pretty cool, i mean i met this guy Burt on the bus to our hotel, he so far is the only person i can stand hanging around.  I met up with this girl Sara who is the one that got us our rooms and everything, she is ok, wierd but ok....So after we get out of the airport we have to catch a bus to our hotel. At this point i'm standing in line with Sara, waiting for this bus while she is in the worst mood and my of course, i'm listening to my IPod and dancing around.  I then go and start hitting on the girl telling people to get on the bus, she was cool, she told me all the hot spots in town.  So we catch the bus witch takes like a hour to get to our hotel, like a whole nother flight.  We get to the hotel, and all together there is going to be like 6 of us will all our shit, which is alot, in this room with 2 beds. So last night a group of us went out, i don't even remember anyones names except the few, Sara Burt, Kaythrine, Josh and i think thats it.  We went bar hoping, it was okay, i drank a lot yet couldn't get a good buzz at all....after we left one of the bars, Burt meets a few girls, him and i go with them and everyone else takes off, not that i cared much about that. We hung out with them for a little, then left them b/c they wanted to go to some dumb club where they are handing out no line no cover cards.  So we leave them and don't know what the hell to do, so we start walking back towards the hotel and stop at this resturant and Burt looks on the menu and it says "Greens" so he asks the guy sitting having a drink thats next to the menu if the greens are good, the guy starts laughing and asks what kinda greens....make the long story short, we sit down with the guy and his girl and order drinks and the most AMAZING frys i've ever had, those were so damn good, Mmmm.  So we sit down and start talking and laughing talking about US vs Canadian girls, good ole times....then we went back to the room and crashed.  

I'm excting right now, b/c i have wireless internet in my hotel room and i didn't know it, so it give me a few more days to keep in touch and finish up stuff......
